## 2. View Module Structure

A **View module** is one folder per screen or cohesive functional area. Keep all layers for that View in one place (vertical slice).

### Recommended layout

```
src/views/foo/                   # or src/features/foo/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ index.ts                     # public barrel вҖ” only what other Views/app consume
в”ңв”Җв”Җ FooView.tsx                  # View entry вҖ” layout, hook wiring, loading/error/empty
в”ңв”Җв”Җ api/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ Foo.ts                   # read model types
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ FooResource.ts           # port interface
в”ңв”Җв”Җ domain/                      # optional
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ validateFoo.ts
в”ңв”Җв”Җ infrastructure/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ dto/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ mappers/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ resources/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ hooks/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ fooQueryKeys.ts
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ useFooQuery.ts
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ useFooViewModel.ts
в”ңв”Җв”Җ context/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ FooProvider.tsx
в””в”Җв”Җ components/                  # presentational pieces private to this View
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ FooList.tsx
    в””в”Җв”Җ FooRow.tsx
```

### App-level shared code

Code reused across multiple Views belongs outside the View folder:

```
src/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ views/                       # View modules (vertical slices)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ shared/                      # cross-View UI primitives, utils, types
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ components/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ hooks/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ api/
в””в”Җв”Җ app/                         # router, root providers, app shell
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ App.tsx
    в””в”Җв”Җ providers.tsx
```

**Rules:**

- A View imports from its own layers and from `shared/` вҖ” not from another View's internal folders.
- Cross-View consumption goes through the other View's `index.ts` public barrel, or through `shared/`.
- Use the project's path aliases (e.g. `@/views/foo`) вҖ” avoid deep relative imports across Views.

### When to split a View

Start with one folder per View. Extract to `shared/` only when a second View genuinely needs the same code. Do not pre-split into multiple packages or micro-libraries prematurely.

